metadata.name: Manu #66
metadata.description:
Manu
---------------

A collector-led exploration of minimalist imperfect line work.

Outputs are generated from a combination of the minter's address, their choice from one of 50 seeds, and options to adjust how the generated surface is presented.

Palettes are named after native New Zealand birds and range from the subdued to the colorful.

There are no especially rare traits so mint what you love :)

---------------

Controls:
S - Export as png
H - Toggle high resolution

metadata.name: Dots #152
metadata.description:
Titled as a play with colors and shapes created from dots, Dots started as a collection on Objkt, extended to 8bidou and had new developments in Exchange Art. It was a dream to be able to make a collection of Dots on Fxhash, now it finally happened. Initially we only had 1 color palette, however, to create more variety, this project has 7 color palettes. To create the palettes we chose 5 famous artists to honor, including Peter Halley, Max Bill, Piet Mondrian, Sophie Taeuber and Lygia Clark, in addition to the palettes created by us. The project has several grids and some new possibilities in addition to the pieces already created on other platforms. It is with great pride and joy that we present this project made with great affection. Enjoy!

Press [S] to save a image

Windswept

Press 's' in live view to download a copy of your image.

You can add the URL parameter 'scale' to scale the size of the image for a higher resolution download (1600x2000 by default). (Warning: large numbers may not work depending on your hardware/browser and can produce a very large download file of ~100mb)

metadata.name: Vorticity #49
metadata.description:
Vorticity is a gpu-accelerated flow field. The particles in the flow field orbit around a set of points that move around over time.

Controls: Click and drag to push particles away. Press the space bar to pause the simulation, and again to resume. While paused, you can press "n" to advance the simulation a single step. Press "r" to restart the simulation (if you change the resolution of the screen after the page loads, you will need to restart to update the resolution).

metadata.name: Zpritez 3D #995
metadata.description:
Generates interactive 3D pixel art sprites.
Each character also has a unique sound effect.
There are a variety of styles and backgrounds.
Click or touch to interact, position tweaks the sound.
Right click to save as a 1920x1080 image.

Code is based on my open source sprite generator ZzSprite.
https://github.com/KilledByAPixel/ZzSprite

Audio is using my open source sound effect system ZzFX.
https://github.com/KilledByAPixel/ZzFX
